WEBVTT

01:17.026 --> 01:18.027
Good morning, Concord.

01:19.449 --> 01:19.709
Good morning.

01:19.729 --> 01:24.475
Everybody excited to be here and back in the routine, back in school, all that stuff.

01:25.236 --> 01:36.148
If you live in about a three mile radius of the Burkett house, I'm sure you heard that collective groan inside Thursday morning on the day that my daughter Aslan affectionately referred to as throw up Thursday.

01:36.609 --> 01:39.192
So she was really excited to get school going again.

01:40.013 --> 01:42.756
My name is Jay Burkett, and I'm a member of the pulpit ministry team.

01:42.936 --> 01:44.498
And if you were not here last week,

01:44.962 --> 01:54.013
We had Derek Spain to fill the pulpit and Derek is the man that the Lord has led our team to recommend to you for the position of interim senior pastor.

01:54.694 --> 02:00.962
And we will make that recommendation in the form of emotion at our regularly scheduled business meeting this Wednesday at 6 30.

02:01.402 --> 02:05.327
So make sure you're here for that this Wednesday 6 30 and we'll make that motion.

02:06.188 --> 02:14.098
We're very excited about it because Lord willing what that will enable our team to do is to focus 100% of our efforts.

02:14.594 --> 02:23.427
and prayers and attention and focus on finding the man the Lord has already found and already appointed to be our next senior pastor here at Concord.

02:23.447 --> 02:24.688
That's exciting to think about.

02:25.109 --> 02:29.756
We're very excited for me to be able to introduce to you once again this morning, Derek Spain.

02:36.085 --> 02:36.606
Thank you.

02:36.626 --> 02:41.052
It's great to be back at Concord and looking forward to all that God has in store for us.

02:41.693 --> 02:42.514
If you have a Bible,

02:42.626 --> 02:44.770
Please open it to Luke, chapter 19.

02:45.591 --> 02:47.915
Like you take your Bible and open to Luke, chapter 19.

02:48.416 --> 02:50.680
And as you're turning there, I'll ask you the question.

02:52.143 --> 02:53.064
So what's your story?

02:55.528 --> 03:00.237
Or maybe another way to say it would be you're talking to someone and you say, hey, tell me a little bit about yourself.

03:01.499 --> 03:04.825
Depending on the setting, that answer comes a little different, right?

03:05.085 --> 03:06.808
So if someone says, what's your story?

03:06.828 --> 03:07.890
Tell me about yourself.

03:08.194 --> 03:14.563
If you're in a work setting, then they're gonna be talking about business and what my job is and our company and things like that.

03:15.304 --> 03:21.713
If it's in a family situation, you're immediately gonna talk about kids and spouse and grandkids and those things.

03:22.374 --> 03:29.624
If you're at a leisure activity, you might talk about how long you've been involved in this hobby or sport or whatever you're talking about.

03:30.645 --> 03:36.914
If you're a church, what's your story, a lot of times, we would think with our spiritual mind on and we would think, ah,

03:37.058 --> 03:39.682
This is my story of faith in Christ.

03:41.144 --> 03:45.390
I'd like to tell you my story of faith in Christ in 20 seconds.

03:46.111 --> 03:46.432
You ready?

03:46.452 --> 03:47.333
You get your time already?

03:48.294 --> 03:49.716
Everybody doesn't have it on a watch anymore.

03:49.736 --> 03:50.437
You have it on your phone.

03:51.499 --> 03:52.300
Here's my story.

03:52.841 --> 04:01.814
There was a time in my life that I was a good person, but I was very selfish, self-centered, and I was spiritually lost.

04:02.815 --> 04:04.658
Somebody told me about Jesus.

04:05.186 --> 04:08.871
And all that he did for me on the cross and how he rose from the dead.

04:08.991 --> 04:10.452
And I placed my faith in him.

04:11.334 --> 04:12.675
He changed me forever.

04:13.556 --> 04:15.839
And now I have purpose and meaning in life.

04:17.121 --> 04:23.448
And I have the promise and assurance of heaven after I die.

04:23.468 --> 04:26.252
So in about 20 seconds, I just share with you my story.

04:26.692 --> 04:28.054
There's a lot more details.

04:28.795 --> 04:30.297
And I'm going to get to some of those this morning.

04:31.738 --> 04:34.642
But how would you tell your story?

04:35.650 --> 04:36.672
of faith in Christ.

04:37.894 --> 04:47.228
Well, one guy, Zacchaeus, would talk about in Luke chapter 19, how salvation came to this house.

04:49.151 --> 05:03.634
As we think about this text today from the Bible, here on all of our campuses and online, as you're listening to this message, I pray that each person would examine your own heart and ask the question,

05:04.162 --> 05:07.546
First of all, do I know Jesus as my Lord and Savior?

05:08.488 --> 05:12.593
Because if He is your Lord and Savior, then you have a story of faith.

05:14.936 --> 05:24.389
And if He is your Savior, I pray that today, through God's Word, you'll be reminded and encouraged and inspired and even equipped to share your story with others.

05:25.049 --> 05:31.538
That it'll be a really good day to celebrate all that God has been doing in your life, is doing now, and wants to do in the future.

05:32.194 --> 05:36.259
And as you share your story with others, that others may come to Christ.

05:36.279 --> 05:42.227
But there may be some on our campuses today, and you don't yet know Jesus as your Lord and Savior.

05:43.349 --> 05:50.638
It may be that you come to church every week, or maybe this is your first time at a church ever in a long time.

05:51.699 --> 05:59.890
But if you were to get real honest with God, you would say, I don't really have a genuine story of faith in Christ.

06:00.034 --> 06:03.580
If you're to answer it, you say, Jesus is not yet my Lord and Savior.

06:03.980 --> 06:04.441
He's not.

06:06.084 --> 06:10.591
The good news for you today is before you leave today, he can be.

06:11.532 --> 06:13.055
He can save you.

06:13.095 --> 06:15.098
He wants to save you.

06:15.879 --> 06:22.029
And so my prayer today, all over our campuses at Concord, is that God would bring salvation to these houses.

06:22.710 --> 06:24.974
That God would bring salvation to the lost.

06:25.835 --> 06:27.698
And for those of us who know Christ,

06:28.034 --> 06:33.902
that today would be a day that we are equipped, inspired, and encouraged and challenged to share our story with others.

06:34.403 --> 06:36.706
Could I ask you to stand please for the reading of God's word?

06:37.948 --> 06:41.432
Luke chapter 19, beginning in verse one.

06:42.033 --> 06:43.115
Here's what the Bible says.

06:44.477 --> 06:47.661
He entered Jericho and was passing through.

06:47.701 --> 06:54.290
There was a man named Zacchaeus who was a chief tax collector, and he was rich.

06:55.251 --> 06:57.234
He was trying to see who Jesus was,

06:57.730 --> 07:01.996
but he was not able because of the crowd, because he was a short man.

07:02.937 --> 07:07.624
So running ahead, he climbed up a sycamore tree to see Jesus, since he was about to pass that way.

07:08.405 --> 07:18.940
When Jesus came to the place, he looked up and said, Zacchaeus, hurry and come down, because today it is necessary for me to stay at your house.

07:20.182 --> 07:23.386
So he quickly came down and he welcomed him joyfully.

07:24.307 --> 07:26.130
All who saw it began to complain,

07:26.466 --> 07:28.689
He's going to stay with a sinful man.

07:29.870 --> 07:35.316
But Zacchaeus stood there and said to the Lord, look, I'll give half of my possessions to the poor Lord.

07:36.257 --> 07:40.762
And if I have extorted anything from anyone, I'll pay back four times as much.

07:41.903 --> 07:53.437
Today, salvation has come to this house, Jesus told him, because he too is the son of Abraham, for the son of man has come to seek and to save the lost.

07:53.937 --> 07:54.738
Let's pray together.

07:55.874 --> 08:07.851
Our Heavenly Father, we thank You that we have worshiped You already this morning through singing, through giving, ties, and offerings, through prayers, through encouraging and fellowshiping with one another.

08:08.632 --> 08:20.608
And now Father, through the teaching of Your Word, we pray through Your Holy Spirit that You would speak to us and that we would not just be hears of the Word, but we would do what it says.

08:21.630 --> 08:24.914
And so Father, my prayer today is that every believer

08:26.018 --> 08:37.012
who hears this message will be encouraged, equipped, and inspired to share their story of faith with others this week.

08:37.032 --> 08:49.046
And Father, also my prayer is that those who hear this message today that are lost, today will be the day of their salvation, that their lives will be changed for all of eternity.

08:49.787 --> 08:52.050
And it's in Jesus' name we pray, amen.

08:55.618 --> 08:56.519
So what's your story?

08:58.201 --> 09:05.289
Let me try to summarize my story in Zacchaeus' story and maybe even frame your story with three phrases.

09:05.309 --> 09:10.375
The first thing we want to think about is my life before I met Jesus.

09:11.336 --> 09:15.060
My life before I met Jesus.

09:15.941 --> 09:17.623
So think about your life in that way.

09:18.424 --> 09:20.306
My life before I met Jesus.

09:20.962 --> 09:22.824
So I grew up in the Dakula area.

09:23.004 --> 09:26.068
Some of you may remember, I sort of shared a little bit about myself last week.

09:27.309 --> 09:28.691
I grew up in the Dakula community.

09:29.272 --> 09:37.201
I'm going to get to my salvation story just a moment, but a little of my background in terms of since I've been out of high school, graduate from Dakula High School.

09:37.902 --> 09:39.483
I went to shorter university.

09:39.503 --> 09:40.465
That's where I met my wife.

09:41.486 --> 09:45.170
I served as a student pastor at Hebrew for 10 years.

09:46.850 --> 09:49.332
Kim and I have been married for 25 years.

09:49.372 --> 09:50.353
We have three children.

09:50.574 --> 09:52.375
Our oldest son, Grant, is 21.

09:52.515 --> 09:56.659
Our middle son, our middle child is a son.

09:56.859 --> 09:57.900
Andy is 18.

09:58.321 --> 09:59.962
Just graduated from D'Cula High School.

09:59.982 --> 10:03.846
And our daughter is 15 in a couple of weeks, and she goes to the Cula High School.

10:03.926 --> 10:05.808
So two boys and a girl, that's her family.

10:07.329 --> 10:08.871
Student pastor, Heaven, for 10 years.

10:08.951 --> 10:11.133
And then the Lord gave me the opportunity to serve.

10:11.613 --> 10:16.658
So we heard this last week as a lead pastor in Lake Placid, New York.

10:16.962 --> 10:28.519
the mountains of New York and was there for ten years serving there, Lake Pastor by this church as the lead pastor, senior pastor, and then also near my time there was a missionary with the North American Mission Board.

10:28.960 --> 10:33.967
And the assignment was to get the gospel to the winter sports athletes of the world.

10:34.488 --> 10:39.375
And so that was where we spent a lot of our time, a lot of our focus was getting the gospel to those guys and girls.

10:40.597 --> 10:41.138
And then

10:41.282 --> 10:52.975
Eight years ago, the Lord called us back to Georgia, and I served as the executive pastor, the number two guy at Hebron, and I was there for about seven and a half years in that role.

10:53.536 --> 10:55.138
And so that sort of brings us to today.

10:56.819 --> 10:58.401
So I grew up in Dicula.

10:58.702 --> 11:02.105
In those days, Dicula was very much a farming community.

11:03.046 --> 11:06.290
My grandparents had cattle farms and

11:06.466 --> 11:11.073
We had an old chicken house on my grandparents house that we would go in and play in.

11:11.093 --> 11:14.618
There weren't any chickens in there any longer, but that was the...

11:14.638 --> 11:16.481
So, here we grew up.

11:16.501 --> 11:23.811
About a mile down the road was a small Baptist church, and that was the church that my family had been part of for generations.

11:24.532 --> 11:25.714
A lot of my family

11:25.858 --> 11:30.404
grandparents, great-grandparents, et cetera, are buried in the cemetery right beside there.

11:30.724 --> 11:34.189
So that was the church where I first heard the stories of Jesus.

11:34.229 --> 11:35.510
We went to Bible school.

11:36.251 --> 11:40.076
That was the place where I first heard the message of salvation.

11:41.038 --> 11:44.883
And so if you were to describe my early life, I would say it this way.

11:45.063 --> 11:47.025
It sort of revolved around three things.

11:47.726 --> 11:53.714
A revolved around church, a revolved around family, and a revolved around sports.

11:53.986 --> 11:55.428
That was sort of me as a kid.

11:55.609 --> 12:00.958
I was a good kid, but church and family and sports.

12:01.038 --> 12:12.757
I played baseball when I was first, sort of playing baseball when I was six, sort of playing basketball when I was eight, playing football when I was 10, because that's when our town offered those sports first, and that's so when I started to play them.

12:14.019 --> 12:20.530
But in terms of spiritually, even though I was a good kid and I knew all the Bible stories, I was lost.

12:21.666 --> 12:28.452
And I knew I was lost because my language all throughout middle school was running towards sinful.

12:29.974 --> 12:34.378
My attitude towards my parents and towards others was not godly at all.

12:35.119 --> 12:38.262
I had no desire to read the Bible to do what Jesus said.

12:38.782 --> 12:42.966
Now I went to church and I knew the Bible stories, but I had no desire to really live it out in my life.

12:43.787 --> 12:51.154
And when I would think about eternity as a young middle schooler, I knew that I was lost.

12:51.746 --> 13:04.605
I knew if at any moment that I died, I knew what the Bible said and it scared me to death because I knew at that moment, I, if I died, was going to go to hell.

13:06.248 --> 13:07.289
That was my condition.

13:08.171 --> 13:13.038
The Bible says all have sinned and come short of the glory of God.

13:14.861 --> 13:17.505
The Bible says there is none that was righteous, no not one.

13:18.466 --> 13:21.170
Zacchaeus was a man

13:21.762 --> 13:23.765
that the Bible tells us a lot about him.

13:24.626 --> 13:25.768
He lived in Jericho.

13:26.669 --> 13:28.712
He was a tax collector, the Bible said.

13:29.613 --> 13:35.201
Many of you know that in those days the Roman government gave the tax collectors a lot of freedom and latitude.

13:35.661 --> 13:48.178
They had to collect the required taxes that the government asked for, but anything that they through coercion or force or any other way could collect above that, they were allowed to keep for themselves.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.802
The Bible says Zacchaeus

13:50.882 --> 13:52.905
was very rich.

13:53.887 --> 13:57.032
So he was a tax collector that was very rich.

13:58.133 --> 14:01.118
He probably was greedy.

14:02.039 --> 14:06.006
He was a guy because of his job was not very liked.

14:06.506 --> 14:10.533
So he was known but not very popular.

14:11.234 --> 14:19.026
Now from some people, those who were just chasing money and possessions, he would have been a guy they would have said very successful.

14:20.194 --> 14:20.935
because he was rich.

14:22.317 --> 14:27.045
We probably know that Zacchaeus may have been pretty miserable.

14:28.447 --> 14:29.830
Money didn't buy him happiness.

14:31.632 --> 14:33.535
Zacchaeus we know was seeking.

14:34.677 --> 14:37.061
It talks about when Jesus was coming to town, he was seeking.

14:37.542 --> 14:38.744
He was seeking a lot of things.

14:38.784 --> 14:40.467
He was seeking answers.

14:40.487 --> 14:41.148
He was seeking.

14:42.169 --> 14:45.575
Zacchaeus was also very, everybody knows was very short.

14:46.276 --> 14:47.538
The Bible tells us this,

14:48.098 --> 14:51.603
Kids many times grew up singing and generations grew up singing the song.

14:51.663 --> 14:57.673
Zacchaeus was a wee little man and a wee little man was he.

14:57.733 --> 15:00.036
That means short kids.

15:00.076 --> 15:00.958
That's what we means.

15:00.998 --> 15:01.639
That means short.

15:02.160 --> 15:03.762
It's an old fashioned word that means short.

15:04.723 --> 15:15.300
Zacchaeus was short and quite frankly in that culture and in any culture, sometimes people who were shorter than everybody else, they feel like they don't.

15:15.800 --> 15:16.882
Are you ready for a little pun?

15:17.026 --> 15:19.469
they feel like they don't measure up, right?

15:19.489 --> 15:21.052
They feel like they don't measure up.

15:21.072 --> 15:23.255
And they literally can't see above the crowds.

15:23.916 --> 15:38.556
And they many times do have a bit of a, you know, sort of complex about things, but it's true actually many people, it doesn't matter if they're short or if they're tall, if they're skinny or if they're bigger, their hair is brown or blonde or red.

15:39.197 --> 15:45.586
People, many times guys, this is just human nature, are dissatisfied with our appearance.

15:46.114 --> 15:48.317
And we get all frustrated about that.

15:49.098 --> 15:51.240
We're too young, we're too old, we're this, we're that.

15:52.001 --> 15:56.807
Zacchaeus was a person just like anybody else that had insecurities.

15:57.828 --> 15:59.089
Perhaps he was lonely.

15:59.810 --> 16:06.558
Perhaps he was in many ways seeking the answers that on this day he was gonna find.

16:07.279 --> 16:13.106
So my question to you is, if I were to ask you the question, what was your life like?

16:13.762 --> 16:17.608
Before you met Jesus, what would you say?

16:18.629 --> 16:22.255
If your life before Jesus, so think about that.

16:23.056 --> 16:25.500
And maybe even on your page, write some things down.

16:26.582 --> 16:28.685
My life before Jesus was.

16:29.566 --> 16:33.011
You may have heard me say it earlier when I said my 22nd testimony.

16:34.333 --> 16:42.706
I was a good person, but I was sinful, self-centered, spiritually lost.

16:43.330 --> 16:43.991
That was me.

16:46.193 --> 16:47.895
I was destined for hell.

16:48.636 --> 16:51.039
What was your life like before Christ?

16:52.140 --> 17:03.673
The reason I ask you that question is because I'm praying for each of you that God would give you the opportunity even this week maybe to share your story with someone else.

17:04.714 --> 17:09.119
And how do you share your story unless you've thought about, this is what my story is.

17:10.420 --> 17:12.082
When you also reflect on

17:12.290 --> 17:13.972
What your life was like before Christ.

17:14.573 --> 17:18.517
You are so grateful for how Jesus has changed you.

17:19.218 --> 17:20.539
So my life before Christ.

17:21.140 --> 17:22.762
My life before I met Jesus.

17:22.802 --> 17:25.265
That was Zacchaeus' story and that was my story.

17:25.505 --> 17:26.186
Here's number two.

17:26.987 --> 17:28.729
How I met Jesus.

17:29.650 --> 17:31.672
How I met Jesus.

17:33.114 --> 17:34.415
Zacchaeus would say it this way.

17:35.517 --> 17:40.242
He would talk about going to a sycamore tree.

17:41.410 --> 17:45.236
Let me tell you how I met Jesus, how he found me.

17:46.919 --> 17:47.900
I was 13 years old.

17:48.962 --> 17:50.564
It was February of 1985.

17:51.245 --> 17:53.689
As a matter of fact, I remember it was February 8th, 1985.

17:54.651 --> 17:58.076
And through the beauty of Google and the internet, I'd be able to verify that that date is correct.

17:59.057 --> 18:02.964
It was a Friday night, and we were having one our church called a youth revival.

18:03.424 --> 18:07.250
So the guest speaker, guest musicians, and they came, and they sang.

18:07.891 --> 18:09.714
And he shared a message of salvation.

18:10.626 --> 18:12.909
As a matter of fact, He shared a message very similar to this.

18:13.690 --> 18:19.037
He shared a message that said that all have sinned and come short of the glory of God.

18:19.177 --> 18:20.659
We've all sinned, we've all messed up.

18:21.461 --> 18:23.103
And the wages of sin is death.

18:23.904 --> 18:30.172
The payment that we deserve for our sin is death, spiritual death, separation from God forever.

18:31.013 --> 18:34.418
But God demonstrates His love towards us in this.

18:35.059 --> 18:37.802
While we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.

18:38.423 --> 18:40.466
So His message was you were

18:40.834 --> 18:50.047
lost because of your sin, but Jesus died on the cross to pay the penalty of your sin that you don't have to face the penalty that you deserve.

18:50.849 --> 18:58.199
And so even though the wages are sent as death, the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.

18:59.001 --> 19:01.464
And so we are sinners and eat of a savior.

19:01.564 --> 19:08.274
Jesus saved, Jesus died that we might be safe and he offers the gift of salvation to everyone who will believe.

19:09.602 --> 19:25.647
The Bible says in Romans chapter 10, verses nine and 10, that if you will confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved because this was the heart you believe under righteousness and with the mouth confession is made to salvation.

19:26.388 --> 19:37.746
So his message and my message, the message of the Bible is that if you will, it's something you believe so much in your heart that you're unashamed to say out loud, is that I believe Jesus died for me and rose again.

19:39.042 --> 19:44.049
And on that night, February of 1985, it's like a spiritual light bulb came on in my heart.

19:45.171 --> 19:51.821
It's like Jesus, yes, He died for the sins of others, but He died for me.

19:52.702 --> 19:54.104
And I need Him to save me.

19:56.167 --> 19:59.372
The Bible says, whoever calls the name of the Lord shall be saved.

20:00.634 --> 20:03.258
We call on His name, we call on His name through prayer.

20:03.799 --> 20:08.786
And on that night, at the end of the worship service, I went and told our pastor, I said,

20:09.154 --> 20:13.259
We were singing a song at the end and I said, I need to give my life to Christ.

20:14.140 --> 20:23.511
And so with one of the gentlemen in our church, I knelt and I prayed and said, Jesus, he told me, he says, listen, Derek, you can pray quietly in your heart if you want to.

20:23.892 --> 20:26.174
But man, if you don't mind, pray it out loud so I can hear it.

20:27.055 --> 20:27.536
And I did.

20:27.596 --> 20:28.277
I prayed out loud.

20:28.297 --> 20:29.518
And I said something similar to this.

20:29.598 --> 20:32.302
I said, Jesus, you died for me.

20:32.322 --> 20:35.986
I am a sinner and I need you to save me.

20:36.546 --> 20:42.354
Jesus, the best I know how, right now by faith, I ask you to come into my heart and save me.

20:43.255 --> 20:45.358
I believe that you died from me and rose again.

20:45.378 --> 20:47.621
I commit my life to you.

20:48.442 --> 20:49.984
Thank you for saving me, Jesus.

20:50.545 --> 20:53.088
Help me to never be ashamed of you.

20:54.850 --> 20:56.032
That's how I met Jesus.

20:57.454 --> 20:59.697
Through his Holy Spirit, he drew me to salvation.

21:00.198 --> 21:06.546
He showed me the truth in his word, and on that night, I asked him to save me, and he did.

21:08.130 --> 21:08.771
How about you?

21:09.893 --> 21:11.795
How did you meet Jesus?

21:13.658 --> 21:15.321
Zacchaeus met him this way.

21:16.442 --> 21:18.365
Zacchaeus heard Jesus was coming to town.

21:19.447 --> 21:27.599
Remember last week if you were here, we talked about if we approached life like Jesus did on mission everywhere, then we would see crowds of people.

21:29.021 --> 21:31.124
And we would feel the compassion of Jesus felt.

21:31.164 --> 21:37.714
And we would hear the call, the call to give, the call to pray, the call to go with the message of salvation.

21:38.754 --> 21:47.203
Jesus saw not just the crowds of people, but he saw the individuals in the crowd, the individuals that need his life.

21:47.223 --> 22:01.579
And on this day, Jesus saw a very short man full of ingenuity, full of drive and desire seeking him, a guy who climbed up in a tree so he could see.

22:01.619 --> 22:04.662
And the Bible says something really interesting in verse five.

22:04.983 --> 22:08.146
It says, when Jesus came to the place,

22:09.570 --> 22:14.157
The place, the place that Zacchaeus met Jesus.

22:15.739 --> 22:20.226
And then Jesus says, would you quickly come down Zacchaeus because I'm going to stay at your house.

22:20.607 --> 22:22.970
So he came down and welcomed Jesus joyfully.

22:23.872 --> 22:24.733
It's interesting, right?

22:25.234 --> 22:28.319
Unfortunately, there were some people who grumbled and complained.

22:28.839 --> 22:31.243
Why is Jesus going to spend time with this sinful man?

22:33.166 --> 22:33.907
A sinful man.

22:33.927 --> 22:38.354
I mean, all the people in the crowd, all the men and women were sinful.

22:39.106 --> 22:40.948
including the people who made this statement.

22:41.889 --> 22:45.374
Jesus just chose to go to the one who was ready to say yes to him.

22:47.216 --> 22:49.098
Jesus could have spent time with any of them.

22:49.419 --> 22:52.583
They would have all been the same boat as Zacchaeus lost in need of a savior.

22:53.164 --> 22:59.912
Jesus chose on that day because of Zacchaeus's heart because of what Jesus and his sovereignty he brought salvation to Zacchaeus.

23:00.393 --> 23:01.554
Where did Zacchaeus

23:02.146 --> 23:03.227
How did he meet Jesus?

23:03.568 --> 23:07.312
He met him on a road in Jericho, and then he met Jesus at his house.

23:07.332 --> 23:12.919
Just like this young lady that was baptized this morning, she met Jesus at her house.

23:14.501 --> 23:16.764
I'm asking you, where did you meet Jesus?

23:17.064 --> 23:25.134
And for some of you, you need to say today on this campus, at all of our campuses, online, I need to meet Jesus in this house.

23:25.895 --> 23:31.922
Wherever you're at, you need to meet Jesus today, inviting him in to be the Lord and Savior of your life.

23:32.610 --> 23:36.115
And you literally could pray a prayer that says, Jesus saved me.

23:37.237 --> 23:39.080
If you understand, he died for you and rose again.

23:39.140 --> 23:43.727
He becomes a savior of your life and will change your life forever.

23:44.368 --> 23:45.590
How did you meet Jesus?

23:46.291 --> 23:49.336
If you already know him, maybe jot some of those things down.

23:49.356 --> 23:56.707
I mean, oh, some of you, you say I met Jesus when I was watching a Billy Graham crusade on TV, or maybe I had a Billy Graham crusade.

23:57.208 --> 24:01.394
I mean, some of you know what him number of just as I am was being played.

24:01.634 --> 24:03.096
when you gave your life to Christ.

24:03.757 --> 24:09.205
Some of you might say, I was out in a field all by myself, just me and God, or down by a river, by a lake.

24:09.786 --> 24:10.967
I was at a church service.

24:11.328 --> 24:12.229
I was in a Bible study.

24:12.249 --> 24:13.451
It was a youth group activity.

24:13.711 --> 24:14.773
I was here, I was there.

24:15.293 --> 24:18.738
My question to you is, how did you meet Jesus?

24:18.979 --> 24:20.561
We're just reading the Bible by yourself.

24:20.621 --> 24:21.562
Did you hear a message?

24:22.003 --> 24:23.405
Did your parents explain it to you?

24:23.685 --> 24:25.308
Maybe a friend, maybe a youth pastor?

24:25.788 --> 24:27.511
How did you meet Jesus?

24:28.712 --> 24:29.874
You need to know this.

24:31.074 --> 24:36.201
so that you haven't settled in your heart, but you also need to know this so you can share it with others.

24:38.264 --> 24:42.490
Because again, I ask you, this week you wanted to go to someone and say, hey, what's your story?

24:43.712 --> 24:45.835
And you want them to tell you the story of faith.

24:45.855 --> 24:50.962
And they tell you something, whatever the best they can, but you just say for a moment, can I tell you my story?

24:52.324 --> 24:54.066
Here's what my life was like before Christ.

24:55.328 --> 24:56.369
Here's how I met Jesus.

24:57.351 --> 24:59.634
How powerful, this should be the regular,

24:59.746 --> 25:04.251
conversation that we're having as believers in Christ.

25:05.713 --> 25:07.575
Here's how I met Jesus.

25:08.656 --> 25:09.397
Number three is this.

25:10.438 --> 25:14.062
How Jesus changed my life.

25:15.103 --> 25:15.824
Let me tell you for me.

25:16.244 --> 25:17.545
Here's how Jesus changed my life.

25:17.946 --> 25:19.287
So I got saved on a Friday night.

25:20.208 --> 25:21.490
The next day was Saturday morning.

25:22.371 --> 25:26.295
My little brother had a basketball game and so I went with my parents and we were watching the game.

25:27.196 --> 25:29.138
And like normal I was hanging out with my buddies.

25:29.634 --> 25:35.542
And like normal, they began to make some comments about some of the girls that were there that were inappropriate.

25:35.983 --> 25:36.283
Got it?

25:36.363 --> 25:36.844
Enough said.

25:38.687 --> 25:47.258
And I remembered there was for the first time in my life the conviction of the Holy Spirit that said to me, I don't need to say things like that anymore.

25:49.401 --> 25:51.645
I don't even need to listen to things like that anymore.

25:53.026 --> 25:58.514
Guys, almost immediately there was a desire to read God's Word.

25:59.394 --> 26:03.518
A desire to live a life of holiness and obedience to God's word.

26:03.939 --> 26:07.703
There was the peace of the Holy Spirit and the conviction of the Holy Spirit in my life.

26:08.744 --> 26:11.286
There was a desire to be obedient in every way.

26:11.346 --> 26:16.231
As a matter of fact, two days after I got saved, I got baptized on Sunday.

26:17.172 --> 26:19.314
Now, let me pause for just a second to say this.

26:19.915 --> 26:21.937
I had grown up going to church, as I said.

26:21.977 --> 26:26.642
I had actually become a church member of that church when I was 10 years old.

26:27.234 --> 26:29.978
because it was sort of expected about that age to become a church member.

26:30.279 --> 26:33.604
And I got baptized when I was 10, but I didn't know the Lord.

26:34.646 --> 26:35.648
I didn't know the Lord at all.

26:36.149 --> 26:42.820
As a matter of fact, you could have seen, again, as I described earlier, the pattern of my life, anywhere except church.

26:42.840 --> 26:43.961
The church had everybody fooled.

26:44.482 --> 26:46.425
They thought I was a good kid, saved.

26:47.107 --> 26:51.354
I knew I was lost, God knew I was lost, until the night I got saved.

26:51.374 --> 26:54.098
So two days after I gave my life to Christ, I got baptized.

26:54.498 --> 26:56.780
Some people might say you got baptized twice.

26:57.000 --> 26:58.962
I would say no the first time I just got wept.

27:00.404 --> 27:04.167
Because baptism is a testimony of faith in Christ.

27:04.187 --> 27:14.117
So there may be some people here on some of our campuses and today at the end of the service you need to come and talk to one of the pastors and say very soon I need to get baptized.

27:14.397 --> 27:16.279
Because I want to be obedient to God's word.

27:16.539 --> 27:21.724
Because your testimony maybe is that you got saved after you got baptized.

27:21.885 --> 27:23.346
You got baptized when you were younger.

27:23.682 --> 27:30.910
But then you gave your life to Christ and I would challenge you to be obedient to God's word to get baptized as a follower of Jesus.

27:30.970 --> 27:32.752
To tell the world I'm a follower of Christ.

27:34.715 --> 27:38.499
Jesus changed my life in so many ways.

27:38.579 --> 27:42.964
He gave me a desire to live for him, a desire for others to know him.

27:42.984 --> 27:48.390
35 years since I got saved, I haven't gotten over it.

27:49.532 --> 27:51.474
I want other people to come into

27:51.682 --> 27:54.606
God's family to know Jesus as their Lord and Savior.

27:55.367 --> 28:08.545
But you know one of the main things that changed immediately, and it's still true to this day, when I gave my life to Christ, when I began to think about eternity, no longer was there any fear.

28:09.847 --> 28:10.067
None.

28:11.389 --> 28:20.722
When I think about eternity today, I know when I close my eyes for the last time on earth and open my eyes,

28:20.898 --> 28:27.087
in eternity, I am going to be in heaven with a Lord forever and ever and ever.

28:27.127 --> 28:32.214
There is such peace in my heart about eternity because of Jesus.

28:33.075 --> 28:36.480
And I ask you, has Jesus changed your life in that way?

28:37.221 --> 28:39.665
Is there a desire for his word, a desire to live for him?

28:40.005 --> 28:42.389
Is there a desire that others would know him?

28:43.170 --> 28:44.311
Is there a desire for holiness?

28:44.331 --> 28:45.914
Let me show you in Zacchaeus's life.

28:46.535 --> 28:48.978
It says in verse eight, but Zacchaeus

28:49.826 --> 28:57.297
stood there, this is in his house, and said to our Lord, to the Lord, look, I'll give half of my possessions to the poor.

28:57.578 --> 28:58.900
Lord, let's stop there for a second.

28:59.541 --> 29:10.478
Zacchaeus, who had accumulated and spent his entire professional life accumulating stuff, realized when he met Jesus, stuffed up, make me happy.

29:10.498 --> 29:11.680
I'm giving half of it away.

29:12.541 --> 29:13.162
Giving it away.

29:13.963 --> 29:18.450
Just in that moment, he gave half of it away to the poor, to bless others who needed it.

29:19.042 --> 29:31.798
And then he went further and said, on a very specific personal level with people, he says, and if I have extorted anything from anyone, I'll pay them back four times as much.

29:34.441 --> 29:39.528
All the people who have been wronged by Zacchaeus, he was going to now bless them.

29:40.088 --> 29:43.312
This is a picture of true repentance.

29:43.332 --> 29:45.375
He didn't do this because Jesus made him.

29:45.795 --> 29:47.858
He did it because God put in his heart.

29:48.034 --> 29:51.037
to want to be obedient and to be a blessing to others.

29:51.277 --> 29:53.839
So he went from greed to generosity.

29:54.540 --> 29:56.442
His life was changed forever.

29:57.403 --> 30:12.777
And Jesus clearly says in verse nine and 10, Jesus told him today, salvation has come to this house because he too is a son of Abraham, not just in terms of ethnicity, but in terms of spirituality.

30:13.057 --> 30:18.002
For the son of man has come to seek and to save

30:18.242 --> 30:18.863
The lost.

30:20.885 --> 30:22.727
So let's wrap it all up and pull it together.

30:23.067 --> 30:24.288
So let's talk about your story.

30:25.950 --> 30:29.414
Some of you, your story today is, I know Jesus is my Lord and Savior.

30:30.775 --> 30:33.618
So I ask you, could you verbalize this week?

30:35.601 --> 30:38.904
Who is it that you could this week tell?

30:38.964 --> 30:42.468
This is my life before Christ, before I met Jesus.

30:43.469 --> 30:44.790
This is how I met Jesus.

30:45.411 --> 30:48.114
This is how Jesus has changed my life.

30:49.250 --> 30:53.516
Because if you're taking notes, I would ask you maybe to write down God as a prayer.

30:53.636 --> 30:56.881
God, give me a chance to share my story this week.

30:58.062 --> 31:03.990
And for some of you, you need to take it a step further, further, because you know whom God's leading you to share with.

31:04.351 --> 31:09.738
And maybe you need to write God, give me a chance this week to share my story with and put their name right there.

31:10.840 --> 31:14.024
You love them that much, you care about them, you want them to know Christ.

31:15.166 --> 31:18.290
You might want to just leave that blank because you say God,

31:18.370 --> 31:27.283
Give me the opportunity to share with many because we share our story so that we can share his story of how he can save them.

31:29.727 --> 31:35.455
We share our faith because we want salvation to come to this house wherever they are every day.

31:36.036 --> 31:41.484
But some of you are here today in this place and across all of our campuses and even online.

31:42.045 --> 31:47.954
And you say today, Derek, if I'm getting really honest, I need to give my life to Christ today.

31:49.442 --> 32:00.413
I want to ask you if that's you, then will you pray with me right now, all of us, if you'll bow your heads and close your eyes across all of our campuses?

32:02.395 --> 32:12.124
This day, if you say, today, I recognize that I need Jesus to be my Lord and Savior.

32:13.866 --> 32:17.810
And the best way I can respond today, the way that I need to respond,

32:19.970 --> 32:21.552
I need to give my life to Christ.

32:23.493 --> 32:27.678
Then with heads bowed and eyes closed across all of our campuses.

32:28.418 --> 32:30.260
Would you just pray something like this to the Lord?

32:30.320 --> 32:32.943
You could pray it out loud or you could pray it quietly in your heart.

32:33.683 --> 32:34.965
God hears you just the same.

32:35.986 --> 32:42.472
But if you say today, I need to give my life to Christ, then would you pray something like this to him right now?

32:43.753 --> 32:48.658
Say, dear Jesus, I am a sinner and I need you to save me.

32:50.210 --> 32:54.694
Jesus, I believe that you died from me on the cross and you rose from the dead.

32:56.136 --> 33:03.163
And right now by faith, I ask you to come into my life, forgive me of my sins, and save me.

33:05.165 --> 33:06.666
Thank you for saving me, Jesus.

33:07.968 --> 33:09.289
I commit my life to you.

33:10.891 --> 33:13.874
Help me to never be ashamed of you.

33:16.456 --> 33:18.258
And now all across our campuses,

33:19.074 --> 33:26.346
We want to tell you how you can respond in the next few minutes to what God's leading you to do.

33:28.550 --> 33:38.026
Here in this place, I want to ask you, did you just pray with me and pray and say, Jesus, I need you to be my savior?

33:39.188 --> 33:44.978
If so, in just a moment, we're going to stand and we're going to sing.

33:45.922 --> 33:49.466
And I want to ask you to have a little bit of courage, but man, you're in a place where people love you.

33:50.187 --> 33:53.350
And man, they are so excited when God's working in people's lives.

33:55.052 --> 34:00.057
Man, this church family will celebrate what God's doing in your life.

34:00.077 --> 34:06.524
So from the youngest person in the room to the oldest, if you say today, I prayed and asked Jesus to be my Lord and Savior.

34:07.165 --> 34:14.012
Maybe you're a person that's been going to church here all your life, or maybe today is the first time you've ever been or you're somewhere in between.

34:14.713 --> 34:15.634
I want to ask you,

34:15.778 --> 34:22.947
If you prayed with me or if you needed to, and you are ready to say today, I want to receive salvation.

34:23.648 --> 34:32.559
When we stand in just a moment, I'm asking you to come to me or one of the other leaders at the front and just take us by the hand and say today, I want to give my life to Christ.

34:32.960 --> 34:36.043
That's the first group of people I want to ask to come in just a moment.

34:36.744 --> 34:41.590
At the same time, there may be others who say, you know what, Derek, you spoke on something that's me.

34:42.351 --> 34:44.434
I am a person who has given my life to Christ,

34:44.770 --> 34:47.073
But since then, I've never been baptized.

34:48.215 --> 34:49.897
And you need to respond.

34:51.139 --> 34:56.986
I'm going to ask you to come and walk down to the front and let us talk to you about that and get that set up as soon as possible.

34:57.848 --> 34:58.589
There may be others.

34:58.929 --> 35:00.251
You want to come and say, you know what?

35:00.571 --> 35:03.655
Well, I could tell this is the kind of church I want to be a member of.

35:04.136 --> 35:11.966
And you want to come to me or one of the other leaders and pastors and say, today I'm making a commitment that Concord is going to be my church home.

35:13.188 --> 35:14.610
And let's get that process started.

35:14.978 --> 35:17.380
There may be others who wanna come and pray for other reasons.

35:17.541 --> 35:18.882
You just wanna come and pray here at the front.

35:18.902 --> 35:19.983
You're invited to do that too.

35:21.064 --> 35:26.169
So I'm gonna ask us after I pray in just a moment for all of us to stand.

35:26.549 --> 35:28.632
And as God's leading you to come, I'm asking you to come.

35:29.212 --> 35:35.038
Lord Jesus, may you have your way now in doing these next few moments, this time of invitation and response.

35:35.719 --> 35:39.062
Help each of us to respond the way you're calling us to respond.

35:39.783 --> 35:42.245
It's in Jesus' name we pray, amen.

35:42.325 --> 35:43.186
As we stand,

35:43.266 --> 35:45.417
If God's leading you to come, you come right now.

35:45.701 --> 35:46.066
Come.

